<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="520" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[826,1441,1305,1418]" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis box="[826,945,1305,1326]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from nominal 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1336,1441,1305,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doris">
<emphasis box="[1336,1441,1305,1326]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">G. doris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the slightly smaller size (mean forewing length = 
<quantity box="[926,1008,1366,1387]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
), thinner forewing pale bands, and larger hindwing spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[826,1441,1450,1594]" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis box="[826,917,1450,1471]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">Biology:</emphasis>
Adult collection dates indicate a single annual generation, with the flight peak between late May and mid June. As discussed under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1295,1387,1511,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doris">
<emphasis box="[1295,1387,1511,1532]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">G. doris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the habitat preference of 
<emphasis box="[1070,1202,1542,1563]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">
G. d. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Slosson" authorityYear="1892" box="[1132,1202,1542,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Arctia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minea">minea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is not clear, but may include wetlands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[826,1441,1626,1740]" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis box="[826,972,1626,1647]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">Distribution:</emphasis>
Southern BC east to NF and NB; because of the paucity of specimens, the southern extent of 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1056,1687,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="doris" subSpecies="minea">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[986,1056,1688,1709]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">minea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and relationship to 
<taxonomicName box="[1298,1407,1687,1708]" pageId="13" pageNumber="520" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="doris">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1350,1407,1687,1708]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="520">doris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is unclear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
